.th UNPACK VII "June 1979"
.sh NAME
unpack \*- unpack the contents of a picture row
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd unpack
(buffer,numpix,pixwd)
.s3
int buffer[depth][rlenth]
.br
int numpix
.br
int pixwd
.s3
int depth
.br
int rlenth
.sh DESCRIPTION
.lp +9 9
buffer	input buffer as supplied to setupb or setupr
.lp +9 9
numpix	number of pixels in
.it buffer
.lp +9 9
pixwd	number of pixels to pack per word
.s3
.lp +9 9
depth	maximum number of rows kept in
.it buffer
.lp +9 9
rlenth	maximum number of columns kept in
.it buffer
.i0
.s3
.it Unpack
will unpack a picture row.
If
.it pixwd
is 0 or 1, no unpacking is done and control returns immediately.
Otherwise, the contents of
.it buffer
are unpacked by shifting the pixels to the left side of
.it buffer
so that there is only one pixel in each word of
.it buffer.
.s3
Function value is -1 on error and +1 on success.
